This paper deals with deep neural networks and image manipulation, which are both topics commonly found in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the representation of images in DNNs, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper raises questions about the properties of natural images, which could potentially fall under the computer graphics (cs.GR) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
